data.chText: 伤害；损害；造成伤害（或损害）的事物
data.enText: the act of causing harm or damage; sth that causes harm or damage
resulting in harm or damage to sb/sth

data.chText: 他全身心地投入工作结果损害了他的健康。
data.enText: He was engrossed in his job to the detriment of his health.
not resulting in harm or damage to sb/sth

simple_means.memory_skill: de 毁 + tri〔= trit〕摩擦 + ment 表名词 → 磨坏了 → 损害

means: 造成伤害(或损害)的事物

data.enText: resulting in harm or damage to sb/sth

data.chText: 他全身心地投入工作结果损害了他的健康。
data.enText: He was engrossed in his job to the detriment of his health.
not resulting in harm or damage to sb/sth

value.def: If something happens to the detriment of something or to a person's detriment, it causes harm or damage to them.

example.ex: Children spend too much time on schoolwork, to the detriment of other activities.
example.tran: 孩子把太多的时间用于做作业，影响了他们参加其他活动。

gramarinfo.label: usu PHR after v, v-link PHR

value.def: If something happens without detriment to a person or thing, it does not harm or damage them.

example.ex: These difficulties have been overcome without detriment to performance.
example.tran: 这些困难都已在不影响业绩的情况下得到了克服。

partsOfSpeech.dec: at 表加强 + trit 摩擦 + ion 表名词 → 摩擦；消耗
con 加强 + trit 摩擦 + e →〔身心〕一再受到摩擦 → 悔恨的
de 毁 + tri〔= trit〕摩擦 + ment 表名词 → 磨坏了 → 损害
trit 摩擦 + e → 像被磨破了一样 → 陈腐的
